subject: p16050730
Findings: In comparison with the study of, the hand of the patient obscures the lower half of the left chest. There is enlargement of the cardiac silhouette with indistinctness of engorged pulmonary vessels, consistent with elevated pulmonary venous pressure. In the appropriate clinical setting, superimposed basilar pneumonia could be considered.
